author: Danielle Harling
title: Kendrick Lamar, ScHoolboy Q, French Montana & More Showed Out On Yams Day
text:
0 
Hip Hop was heavily present at Madison Square Garden yesterday (January 18), as fans showed up to celebrate Yams Day , an annual musical celebration held to honor the late A$AP Yams . 
The concert, which went down on the second anniversary of Yams’ death , boasted expected appearances from those in his A$AP Mob crew, but also featured a handful of surprises. 
TDE was in the house as both ScHoolboy Q and Kendrick Lamar put on for the crowd. Q dived into his Blank Face LP track “Dope Dealer,” while K-Dot got the audience hype as he performed “m.A.A.d city.”
